  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>The Lodge Hemera Apartments are on a self catered basis. Each apartment has a fully equipped kitchen with a hob, multi-function oven, fridge and range of appliances. The supermarket is just opposite the residence. </p>
<p>Alternatively, we've partnered up with Huski who provide premium oven ready meals across the French Alps. Huski will deliver your meals directly to your accommodation in time for your arrival, all you'll have to do is cook. If you'd like to know more, please click <a data-udi="umb://document/341dc2e969e244a9a524ec35d94ae575" href="/{localLink:umb://document/341dc2e969e244a9a524ec35d94ae575}" title="Huski - food &amp; drink delivery service">here</a> for further details.</p>]]></cateringDescription>
  <deactivateThisPage>0</deactivateThisPage>
  <description><![CDATA[<p>The Lodge Hemera apartments are spacious and furnished to a high standard, making them ideal for a week in the mountains. They are an excellent option, as they are only a few minutes walk from the ski lifts and located in the centre of <a data-udi="umb://document/4c93b881bd494483871697b278b37899" href="/{localLink:umb://document/4c93b881bd494483871697b278b37899}" title="La Rosière">La Rosière</a>, where you can find a variety of shops, bars and restaurants. There's a cosy reception and lounge area with a fireplace, as well as fantastic spa facilities including a heated pool, sauna, and whirlpool.</p>
<h2>Leisure facilities</h2>
<p>After a day of exploring the slopes, the residence has a lovely wellness area available for you to use - including a pool, whirlpool and sauna. If you want to train for your next ski adventure, there is a cardio room with a range of equipment. If you are feeling a bit achy, a range of massages and treatments are available for a local fee. </p>
<p>Meet up with friends and family in the welcoming communal lounge and reception area, there is plenty of seating and fireplaces dotted around - perfect for warming up in front of with a book. </p>
<h2>Well equipped apartments</h2>
<p>All of the apartments are finished to a high standard, and are equipped with everything you need for a week in the mountains including a lounge area, balcony with resort or mountain views and comfortable bedrooms. Each apartment has a fully equipped kitchen with an oven, hob, fridge and various other appliances, so you can whip up meals from the comfort of your own apartment - plus if you want to try some local cuisine, fondue and raclette sets are available to rent from the reception (subject to availability). On the days where you don't feel like cooking La Rosière has a range of restaurants which cater for a variety of different tastes, which are just a short walk away.</p>]]></description>
